		<title>Secret scanning updates &#8211; June 2026</title>
		<link>https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-17-secret-scanning-updates-june-2026</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Allison]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 19:23:42 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-17-secret-scanning-updates-june-2026</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>Since our last pattern update, we&#8217;ve expanded secret scanning&#8217;s detection coverage with new partners, more patterns blocked by push protection by default, additional validity checks, and richer metadata for leaked&#8230;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-17-secret-scanning-updates-june-2026">Secret scanning updates &#8211; June 2026</a> appeared first on <a href="https://github.blog">The GitHub Blog</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<html><body><p>Since our <a href="https://github.blog/changelog/2026-04-14-secret-scanning-pattern-updates-and-product-improvements/">last pattern update</a>, we&rsquo;ve expanded secret scanning&rsquo;s detection coverage with new partners, more patterns blocked by push protection by default, additional validity checks, and richer metadata for leaked secrets.</p>
<h2 id="detectors-added" id="detectors-added" ><a class="heading-link" href="#detectors-added">Detectors added<span class="heading-hash pl-2 text-italic text-bold" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></h2>
<p>Secret scanning now automatically detects the following new secret types in your repositories. This release adds two new partners (Cloudsmith and Meraki), significantly expands GitLab token coverage, and adds detectors for Elastic, Slack, Supabase, DataDog, and VolcEngine.</p>
