<p><code>Partner</code> secrets are automatically reported to the secret issuer when found in public repositories through the <a href="https://docs.github.com/code-security/secret-scanning/secret-scanning-partnership-program/secret-scanning-partner-program">secret scanning partnership program</a>.</p>
<p><code>User</code> secrets generate secret scanning alerts when found in public or private repositories.</p>
<h2 id="push-protection-defaults-expanded" id="push-protection-defaults-expanded" ><a class="heading-link" href="#push-protection-defaults-expanded">Push protection defaults expanded<span class="heading-hash pl-2 text-italic text-bold" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></h2>
<p>The following detectors are now included in push protection by default. Repositories with secret scanning enabled, including free public repositories, will have commits containing these secrets automatically blocked.</p>
