		<title>Copilot individual plan sign-ups are reopening</title>
		<link>https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-17-copilot-individual-plan-sign-ups-are-reopening</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Allison]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 14:10:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-15-copilot-individual-plan-sign-ups-are-reopening</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>We&#8217;re reopening sign-ups for GitHub Copilot Student, Pro, Pro+, and Max plans gradually over the next couple of weeks for new subscribers. If you&#8217;ve been waiting to get started with&#8230;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-17-copilot-individual-plan-sign-ups-are-reopening">Copilot individual plan sign-ups are reopening</a> appeared first on <a href="https://github.blog">The GitHub Blog</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<html><body><p>We&rsquo;re reopening sign-ups for GitHub Copilot Student, Pro, Pro+, and Max plans gradually over the next couple of weeks for new subscribers. If you&rsquo;ve been waiting to get started with Copilot, select the <a href="https://github.com/features/copilot/plans?cft=copilot_lo.features_copilot&amp;utm_campaign=Enterprise&amp;utm_medium=referral&amp;utm_source=github">plan</a> that fits your needs. If your preferred option isn&rsquo;t available yet, check back soon.</p>
<p>If you find that you&rsquo;re using more than what&rsquo;s included in your current plan, we&rsquo;ve made some updates to help you get the best experience:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Upgrade to unlock more included usage:</strong> When approaching your included and additional usage limits, you&rsquo;ll see prompts to upgrade to the next tier. You only pay the price difference between plans. Upon upgrading, you immediately get access to the new plan&rsquo;s total included usage, minus what you&rsquo;ve already used this month.
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Pay as you go and stay on your current plan:</strong> You don&rsquo;t need to switch plans to keep going. If you&rsquo;ve exhausted your included credits and hit your additional spending limit, you can pay for the additional usage you&rsquo;ve already consumed, giving you continued access without switching plans.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p>Changes to the upgrades and continued usage experiences are effective immediately.</p>
<p><a href="https://docs.github.com/copilot/about-github-copilot/subscription-plans-for-github-copilot">Learn more about GitHub Copilot plans</a> or join the <a href="https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/197089">discussion</a> within GitHub Community.</p>
<p><img decoding="async" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/25f69164-faf9-4779-86a5-fd6176a9ae2b" alt="social"></p>
</body></html>
<p>The post <a href="https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-17-copilot-individual-plan-sign-ups-are-reopening">Copilot individual plan sign-ups are reopening</a> appeared first on <a href="https://github.blog">The GitHub Blog</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
