		<item>
		<title>GitHub Models is no longer available to new customers</title>
		<link>https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-16-github-models-is-no-longer-available-to-new-customers</link>
		
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Allison]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 20:24:41 +0000</pubDate>
				<guid isPermaLink="false">https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-16-github-models-is-no-longer-available-to-new-customers</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>We are retiring GitHub Models. As a first step, new customers can no longer use it. If your organization or enterprise have not previously used GitHub Models, you won&#8217;t see&#8230;</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-16-github-models-is-no-longer-available-to-new-customers">GitHub Models is no longer available to new customers</a> appeared first on <a href="https://github.blog">The GitHub Blog</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/loose.dtd">
<html><body><p>We are retiring GitHub Models. As a first step, new customers can no longer use it. If your organization or enterprise have not previously used GitHub Models, you won&rsquo;t see it and can&rsquo;t start new usage.</p>
<p><strong>If you are an existing GitHub Models customer, nothing changes today.</strong> You can continue using the playground, API, and models as usual. We will share more details, including timelines, as we move toward full retirement.</p>
<h3 id="whats-changing" id="whats-changing" ><a class="heading-link" href="#whats-changing">What&rsquo;s changing<span class="heading-hash pl-2 text-italic text-bold" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></h3>
<p>New organizations and enterprises without existing GitHub Models usage no longer have access to GitHub Models, on both free and paid plans.</p>
<p>Existing customers with active usage are not impacted by this change and can continue using GitHub Models for now. For new projects that need AI model access, <a href="https://ai.azure.com/">Azure AI Foundry</a> offers a broad model catalog.</p>
<p>To learn more, <a href="https://docs.github.com/github-models">check out our docs about GitHub Models</a>. You can also join our <a href="https://github.com/orgs/community/discussions/categories/models">community discussions</a> to ask questions and share feedback.</p>
</body></html>
<p>The post <a href="https://github.blog/changelog/2026-06-16-github-models-is-no-longer-available-to-new-customers">GitHub Models is no longer available to new customers</a> appeared first on <a href="https://github.blog">The GitHub Blog</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
